Bedded kfs>ch>ep altered metasediment - bedding subparallel to LCA. Small offset faults at high angles to bedding. Carbonate microcrackleveining. Disseminated to patchy to interbedded calcite throughout.

Fine grained kfs>ch altered metasediment with sparse occasional epidote (cpx?) alteration rims interbedded with recrystallised calcite. Patchy sericite alteration. Microfractures in pelite at high angle to bedding.

Bedded fine grained kfs>ch altered metasediment with abundant zones of intense kfs alteration (bright red/pink). Minor carbonate as fracture infill. Microfaulted beds - rare rotation due to faulting. Sparse epidote alteration and zones of minor brecc

Foliated/bedded fine grained kfs/ch altered metasediment with zones of intense kfs alteration interbedded with recrystallised calcite with minor kfs alteration. Zones of epidote (cpx?) alteration of calcite interbeds and rimming pelitic beds.
Faulted to brecciated fine grained kfs/ch altered metasediment as previous. recrystallised calcite breccia infill and minor interbeds.

Intensely brecciated fine grained kfs/ch altered pelite (ch rimming kfs) clasts in recrystallised limestone breccia. Pelitic clasts range in size from <<1mm to 3cm bands. Weakly foliated at high angle to LCA.
Undulately bedded to brecciated from microfaulting fine grained bedding selectvie kfs/ch alteration. Zones of epidote alteration. Rare quartz beds/patches.

Fine grained kfs>ch altered metasiltstone interbedded with fine grained recrystallised limestone. Finely brecciated clasts of pelite in carbonate interbeds. Minor epidote alteration and cps(?) rims on kfs beds. Microfractured perpendicular to bedding
Banded to interbedded kfs alt metasiltstone and ch alt metasiltstone. Carbonate microfractures. Minor faults offsetting bedding. Sparse epidote alteration.
Brecciated and sheared clasts of kfs/ch altered metasiltstone variably banded to floating in mgr recrystallised sandy limestone matrix.

Variably Kfs<->Ch altered fine grained bedded pelite with occasional >30cm zones of float breccia as previous. Pelite is crackle veined with bright pink kfs veining. Later carbonate crackle veining. Patchy sericite on fracture planes. Rubbly broken c
Predominantly float breccia as previously described with clasts of kfs/ch altered metasiltstone floating in carbonate matrix. Interbedded with short intervals of >90% pelite as previosuly described.

Metacarbonate/marble. Variably foliated/bedded recrystallised weakly silicified and kfs altered carbonate strongly fractured and crackle veined with ch infill. Short intervals of bedded strongly ch altered reduced metasediment.
Fault zone through chlorite altered quartz biotite metasediment with patchy kfs alteration.

Metacarbonate/marble. Variably foliated/bedded recrystallised weakly silicified and kfs altered carbonate strongly fractured and crackle veined with ch infill. Short intervals of bedded strongly ch altered reduced metasediment.
Rubbly interval -brittle fracturing - through massive chlorite altered fine grained quartz biotite metasediment. Weakly brecciated.
Strongly brecciated strongly kfs altered recrystallised limestone with chlorite infill.
Medium grained subangular to angular quartz sand with silty matrix. Polymict dropstones up to 12cm - predominantly granodiritic composition.
Very fine grained clay/siltstone. Fractured along bedding planes. Occasional dropstones of sedimentary/volcanic composition. Conformable up/downhole contacts with sandier unit.
Medium grained subangular to angular quartz sand with silty matrix. Polymict dropstones up to 12cm - predominantly granodiritic composition.
Unfoliated intensely brecciated metapelite clasts with variable ch>>hm/kfs alteration supported in weakly recrystallised calcite matrix. uphole (basement) contact sub-parallel to LCA.

Massive mottled chlorite altered pelite and calcite distributed in equigranular texture similar to granodiorite. Zones of HRE replacing calcite/veining into rock - predominantly in zones of reduced carbonate %age.

Foliated chlorite altered metapelite brecciated and matrix supported in calcite matrix. Variable hematite/kfs alteration of matrix and patchy kfs alteration of metapelite. Speckled angular elongate clasts with intense sericite alteraion up to 4mm.

Finely/intensely brecciated chlorite +/- sericite altered metapelite matrix supported in weakly hm-altered calcite. Brecciated clasts predominantly ~4mm with rare 1-2cm foliated chlorite altered metapelite clasts.

Brecciated chlorite +/- sericite altered pelite as previous in variably hm/ch altered calcarous matrix. Breccia clasts generally coarser grained and more abundant than in previous interval. Coarser grained clasts with kfs alteration halos and microve

Matrix supported elongate brecciated clasts of chloite>>kfs altered metapelite in calcareous matrix. Fine grained brecciated pelite with complete sericite replacement. pelite beds broken perpendicular to bedding planes - breccia foliation parallel to
Massive moderately kfs altered recrystallised limestone with very finely brecciated (<1mm) ch/se altered pelite and rare clasts of ch altered pelite.

Banded to brecciated chlorite altered pelite beds up to 3mm thick interbeded with 2-15cm beds of kfs-altered carbonate. Fine grained pelite clasts (<2mm) within carb matrix completely altered to sericite.
Brecciated clasts of hematite->chlorite->sericite altered metapelite with ch->se alteration rims within massive hm/kfs altered calcite matrix. No visible foliation. Faulted downhole contact.

Foliated algal(?) limestone with pervasive vuggy texture. vugs with spar cement. clayey chorite selv. faults at up and downhole contact. Foliation/lamination direction parallel to LCA. Foliations on either side of unit almost perpendicular to LCA.

Banded to brecciated chlorite altered pelite beds up to 3mm thick interbeded with 2-15cm beds of kfs-altered carbonate. Fine grained pelite clasts (<2mm) within carb matrix completely altered to sericite.

Massive to weakly foliated brecciated hematite <-> chlorite altered metapelite matrix supported in calcite matrix. Sericite alteration of smaller clasts in the matrix. Greater concentration of pelite from previous intervals in DrillHole.

Variably foliated brecciated metapelite clasts in recrystallised weakly kfs/hm altered calcite matrix as previous. Clasts are variably Ch/Se/Hm altered with Ch alteration rimming Hm alteration and Se-alteration completely replacing clasts.

Massive brecciated  carbonate with strong chlorite infill. Shear textures. Minor styolotic texture. Patchy kfs alteration of carbonates. Very minor expresson of fault plane via faint slickenslides at DH contact.
Massive poorly sorted psammite/comglomerate. Clast supported. Clast composition predominantly quartz with minor lithics. Calcareous cement. Faulted downhole contact.
Strongly milled clayey fault zone. Predominantly chlorite selvedge with subangular to subrounded clasts of quartz +/- kfs.

Massive plagioclase andesite. Speckled chlorite alteration. Pervasive weak-moderate hematite alteration. Hematite dusted plag phenocrysts. Conformable downhole contact with successive flow. Isolated 2-3mm patches of sericite alteration.

Massive plagioclase phyric andesite. Cumulate texture at conformable UH contact (younging downhole?). Speckled chlorite alteration. Weak-moderate hematite alteration throughout. Hm-dusted phenocrysts.  Isolated 2-3mm patches of sericite alteration.
Massive volcanic breccia. Clasts are entirely of andesitic composition. Minor pathchy white mica alteration of some clasts. White mica alteration of gmass and clasts at downhole contact.

Finely bedded very fine grained siltstone. Uphole contact appears to be infilling fractures in volcanic breccia (younging downhole?). Soft sediment deformation textures & minor brittle faulting. Bed selective qtz/hm -> jasperoidal alt. w.mica alt @ D
Massive volcanic breccia. Clasts are entirely of andesitic composition. Minor pathchy white mica alteration of some clasts.
Finely bedded very fine grained siltstone. Soft sediment deformation textures & minor brittle faulting.
Massive volcanic breccia. Clasts are entirely of andesitic composition. Minor pathchy white mica alteration of some clasts.
Finely bedded very fine grained siltstone. Soft sediment deformation textures & minor brittle faulting. Thin bands of vbx near downhole contact. Faulted from 419.8-420.2m
Massive volcanic breccia. Clasts are entirely of andesitic composition. Minor pathchy white mica alteration of some clasts. Rubby broken core throughout interval

Interbedded silt and sandstone. Graded bedding at ~427m suggests younging downhole. Soft sediment deformation textures & minor brittle faulting. Faulted downhole contact - strong slickenslides. Fault plane subparallel to LCA.
Massive plagioclase>quartz dacite. Quartz eyes and quartz/calcite microveining. Weak speckled HRR alteration. Broken rubbly core from 439.4m

Variably pseudobrecciated and flow banded dacite. Minor quartz phenos. Feldspar phenos are predominantly altered to sericite. Zones of pseudobrecciation show chlorite/calcite crackle microveining and variable ch/hm alt.
Strongly sericite altered fault zone. Predominantly broken core with patches of compotent dacite as previous. Milled clasts show strong HRR alteration. Stressed fractured core near UH/DH contacts.
Variably flow banded massive rhyolite. Feldspar laths predominantly altered to sericite. Carbonate microveins.
Fault zone through previously described dacite. Strong sericite alteration on fault planes and rubbly core.
Variably flow banded massive rhyolite. Feldspar laths predominantly altered to sericite. Carbonate microveins.
Massive to weakly flow banded fine grained aphanitic dacite. Quartz microveins. minor sericite/chlorite alteration coincident with minor fractures.
Massive medium grained strongly sericite altered volcaniclastic. patchy white mica alteration.
Massive feldspar quartz dacite. Reduced chlorte/sericite alteration from previous intervals. Increased plagioclase. Potentially andesitic composition. Calcite microveins to thin <1cm vein breccias.
Lite red/brown soil/regolith
Bleached white oxidised bulldog shale
yellow/red oxidised bulldog shale
yellow/orange bulldog shale
black fresh bulldog shale
Lite grey/white sandstone - cadna owie sandstone
PCD into basement basalt with sericite/chlorite alteration

Basalt. Fine grained with no amygdales. Nonmagnetic with strong sericite and moderate chlorite alteration. Chlorite alteration increases down hole. Late stage carbonate veins with variable hematite dusting/colouration. Small leucoxene grains.

Major and wide fault zone. Basalt with sericite alteration and small leucoxene grains. Increase in chlorite alteration with clays on fault surfaces. Late stage carbonate veins have hematite colouration.
Pale green SE>CH>HM altered fine grained basalt. Crackle brecciated with cb infill and lesser CH veinsand blebs.

Fault zone consisinting of intensely SE>CH and clay altered basalt. Predominantly texturally destroyedand friable (minor zones of solid rock <50cm). Small (<10cm wide) QT+KF+SE(after BI?) granitoid veinwith trace PY blebs. EOH.
Mix of silcrete-soil-and other material
v-fine grained. 9-12 bleached white then red/pink. Oxidised bulldog shale.
V-fine grained. orange then yellow/grey. Oxidized bulldog shale.
Black. clay consistancy. v-fine grained. reduced bulldog shale
Sandstone. rounded to sub-angular. medium tp coarse grained quartz. well sorted. cadan-owie sandstone
Sand matrix + siltstone black, diamectite
Variably silicified bedded dolomite. Poorly sorted with qtz grains up to sand sized matrix. Minor<1m horizons of fgr sst ox-spots & serof fracs. Foliated HRE <V with haem-selvage
Variably silicified bedded dolomite. Poorly sorted with qtz grains up to sand sized matrix with crackled brecciation.

Variably silicified bedded dolomite. Poorly sorted with qtz grains up to sand sized matrix. Minor<1m horizoVariably silicified bedded dolomite. Poorly sorted with qtz grains. Increased oxidation spots.

Variably sericitised bedded fine grained siltstone and dolomitic silstsone +/- sandy horizones. Microveins with HRE infill and selvage. Se-alt predominantly occurs in fractures horizons. Mottled oxidation spots - varying in intensity and pervasivenes
Puggy fault zone. Clayey matrix is red-brown +/- purple hematite altered. Milled to brecciated clasts of strongly sericitised siltstones.

Bedded fine grained siltstones and silty dolomites with as previous. Alteration paragenesis is 1) pervasive hematite 2) sericite alteration along and around fractures 3) purple earthy hematite overprint.
Puggy fault zone. Clayey matrix is red-brown +/- purple hematite altered. Milled to brecciated clasts of strongly sericitised siltstones.
Pale cream/pink bedded variably sericitised styolitic dolomite. Sparry calcite in minor fractures +/- trace pyrite growth on free surfaces.

Pale cream/pink bedded variably sericitised styolitic dolomite. Sparry calcite in minor fractures +/- trace pyrite growth on free surfaces. Appearance of vughs with sparry calcite +/- trace pyrite - increased pyrite from previous interval.
Massive hematite altered dolomite with patchy redox mottling and HRE veining. Minor styolites. Disseminated specular hematite(?) throughout.

Hematite altered silty dolioomite with strong pervasive sericite alteration. Increased alteration along fracture planes at high angles to bedding. Angular broken core - broken predominantly along bedding. Fissility likely a function of sericitisation
Massive sandy dolomite. Sands are mgr-cgr. Massive vfg dolomitic infill. Patchy specular hematite up to 1cm across. Irregular HRE microveining.

Micro-crackle fractured dolomitic siltstone. Strong sericite alteration along fracture planes and as halos around fracs. Thicker beds with pseudobrecciation/mottling from sericite alteration overprinting earlier hm alteration
Massive fine grained HRE-altered dolomite. Crackle veining with increased HRE alteration. Later vuggy/sparry calcite filled fractures crosscut crackle veins. Weak oxidation mottling.
Massive to weakly bedded grey dolomite. Variably styolitic. Abundant late carbonate veins with sparry calcite growth. Minor trace pyrite +/- speciular hematite growth on spar surface.
Massive to weakly bedded grey dolomite. Variably styolitic. As previous without vuggy carbonate veins.
Massive to weakly bedded brown/red/purple dolomite. Early carbonate veins with hematite staining.
Variably brecciated light grey and purple/brown dolomite. Matrix is predominantly red/purple hematite with patchy hsp.

*First true red HRE. Strongly silicified and metasomatised siltstone. Reduced white mica at UH CNT with brittle frac arrays.Zones of si+ch-alt with patchy red HRE. Weakly bxd in ch-alt zones. Proximal to intrusive? No igneous rock observed.
Strongly chlorite altered interbedded siltstone and sandstone. Faulted downhole contact.
Massive to weakly bedded silty sandstone. Strongly chlorite altered in zones. Geopetal of Hematite-altered siltstone infilling crack/fracture suggests younging uphole.
Variably to moderately brecciated silty/sandy dolomite. Se+/-Ch alteration along fractures. Variable se+/-Hm alteration away from fractures.

*Possibly sandy dolomite. Massive vfg md red hm-altered felsic tuff. sub1mm xtals - matrix supported. zones of wht mica +/-hm veining assoc with microcrackle. No visible sed structures. Weakly dolomitic matrix
Matrix supported conglomerate. pervasive hematite alt of matrix. Clasts are predominantly quartz - ~1-6mm - sub-angular to sub rounded .Very fine grained massive dolomite matrix
Massive sandy dolomite as previously described. Strong pervasive hm alteration.

Strongly sericite altered siltstone/silty dolomite. Strong fissility developped along bedding leaving to wedge fractures. Hematite alteration of silty/clayey infill. Infill is visually similar to dolomites from uphole.
Variably hm/se altered bedded silty dolomite. Crackle fractured with cb+/-hm infill. Minor sericite alteration associated with fracturing.
Crackle fractured silicified siltstone. Large fractures with irregular sandy red/brown dolomite infill. no geopetals. Fractures filled with hematite

Massive styolitic sandy dolomite. Irregularly oriented dolomitised cb+/-hm veins average 6mm. hematite crackle veining as previous. Hm+/-se in styolites. Reduced intensity of pervasive hm alt from prev. intervals.
Variably sericitised weakly stressed/fractured silty/sandy dolomite. Massive texture. Pervasive SE-alt from 337.8-339.4
Strongly sericite altered fissile fault zone. Fissility a product of bedding and sericite alteration. Hematite alteration of clayey gouge.
Weakly bedded variably conglomeretic sandy dolomite. sand grains are coarse grained. Hematite+/-carbonate filled crackle veining as previous.

Bedded red/purple/brown dolomite as previous. Reduced sandy grain size and increased frequency of interbeds. Veining and crackle as previous. Irregular patches of microcrystalline tuff(?) between 351-352m. Posible zon of hematite altered tuff in this
Fine grained felsic tuff. Predominantly quartz +/- vfg ch+hm caught in matrix. variable grain size. 1cm band of ch alt at DH Cnt. Chilled margins. Ch-alt in fractures.

Variably bedded sandy hm-alt dol as rpev with minor patches of vfg tuff. Pol-clast supported breccia with tuff+sed+ch-alt clasts from 373-373.2m. Soft sed deformation textures assoc with tuffaceous zones.
Sheared fault through sericitised felsic tuff. Clasts of quartz/sil up to 1cm. Minor hm alt.
Massive red/brown strongly hematite altered weakly dolomitised fine grained volcanic tuff. irregular beds/laminations of microcrystalline silica.
Massive brecciated pale pink/cream dolomite with hematite altered matrix. Clasts are crackle fractured and average 70-80% of rock with poor clast size sorting.
Massive aphanitic basaltic andesite. Leucoxene phyric. Minor amygdals with se>>cb>hm infill. plag phenocrysts are vfg and hm-altered.
Massive brecciated pale pink/cream dolomite with hematite altered matrix. Clasts are crackle fractured and average 70-80% of rock with poor clast size sorting.
As previous, strongly HM altered, massive to weakly brecciated SDO. Faulted upper and lower contacts.
Massive variably brecciated, cb micro veined, variably HM altered dolomite. Sharp alteration fronts.
Massive dolomite, strongly stylolitic, abundant porosity in vuggy veins. Trace pyrite in vugs (with habit of cpy?). Pervasive hematite altered.
Intense TED HM altered. Sharp UH and DH contacts. DH contact  appears to be conformable. CB micro veining/crk.
Strongly fractured massive dolomite. Variably HM altered. Earthy HM clayey infill of crackle. Minor <10 cm earthy HM matrix supported breccia. From 444.1 - 446.6 m strong hematite altered interval.

Brownish-red pink brecciated DOL with minor brownish red dolomitised SSL interlayers. Less intense BXD compared to previous interval. Between 556 - 557 m layers w. quartz grains, poss. quartz SST. Pervasive HM altd with varying intensities, CB veinin
Brownish red dolomitised siltstone with minor dolomite interlayers. Pervasive hematite altered with varying intensities, CB veining. Poss also pervasive potassium enriched/k-fsp altn?
Reddish brown soil.
Brownish yellow siltstone with clay fragments - Oxidised Bulldog Shale.
Yellowish white shalesiltstone - Oxidised Bulldog Shale.
Dark grey shale - Fresh Bulldog Shale.
Light grey-white quartz sands - Cadna-Owie Sands.
Grey diamictite - Boorthana Formation.
Grey-red dolomite, might be basement.
Pink-red dolomite with minor thin dolomitised siltstone interlayers. CB veined, weak-moderate HM altered.
Brown-green fine grained basalt, minor amygdales. CB veining and amygale infill, minor leucoxene.Weak-moderate CH altered.
Pink-red dolomite with minor thin dolomitised siltstone interlayers. CB veined, weak-moderate HM altered.
Green fine grained basalt, minor amygdales. CB veining and amygale infill, minor leucoxene. ModerateCH altered. Chilled margins.
Pale pink dolomite with intercalations of finely laminated purple brown siltstone. Minor cross-cutting CBveins. Weak HM alteration and patchy weak SE>SI alteration.
Fault gouge. HRE caly altered.
Pale pink dolomite with intercalations of finely laminated purple brown siltstone. Minor cross-cutting CBveins. Weak HM alteration and patchy weak SE>SI alteration.
Dark green fine grained basalt. Minor amygdales. Chilled margins. Moderate CH alteration. Mildly magnetic - primary(?) MT.
Pale pink stylolitic dolomite with intercalations of finely laminated brown purple siltstone.
Dolomite w/ siltsone as previous but now crackle brecciated and fracture veined. CB (CASiderite?) infill.Faulted zones consisting of milled clasts and CH+SE+CB alteration.
Pale green to pink SE>CH altered dolomite intercalated w/ SECH altered intercalations (ex-siltstone).

Pale pink stylolitic dolomite w/ intercalations of finely laminated fgr BRN PPL siltstone. Siltstone is vfgr qtzose w/ HRE clay cement which is also present in stylolites. vfgr PYHSP(?) w/in stylolites & fracs (<1%). Mild BX. Pnk CA veining. Rare CH
Pink brown stylolitic dolomite w/ intervals of brn ppl fgr laminated siltstone, as previous, but increased brecciation.
Breccia - Faulted + sheared SE+CH alt grn mafic volcanic intercalated w/ sheared and fractured pinkdolomite (KF+Hm alt). Fgr-Mgr disseminated PY fracture fill (~1-2%). CH+CA+ patchy SI alteration.

Mottled green CH+SE altered mafic volcanic. Vfgr sericitic groundmass with mgr ch altered ex-pyroxenes and (rare) feldspar laths. Fgr dissem leucoxene throughout. Crackle BX with CH infill. Mgr dissem PY(~1%) (some replacing PX). Chilled margins.
Pink green variably CH+SI+KF(pink) altered dolomite intercalated with mustard brown cherty silicified ex-siltstone(?). CA+F veining.

Green brown crackle brecciated mafic volcanic. CH+SE+K alteration. Preferential CH alteration of mgrphenocrysts (ex-PX?) and SE+K alteration of fgr groundmass. Dissem fgr LX and fgr-mgr PY (~1%). CBcrackle infill.
Fault gouge. Foliated. Predominantly brown (HRE) and green (ex-CH?) clay. Minor milled clasts of CHaltered volcanic.
Green brown mafic volcanic as per (442.5 - 443.8 m). SE+CB crackle infill.
CH+SE+MT+SI breccia. Sheared fault zone. PY blebs occuring as fracture fill and replacement of clasts(~3%). Minor Fluorite.

Green brown crackle brecciated mafic volcanic. CH+SE+K alteration. Preferential CH alteration of mgr phenocrysts (ex-PX?) and SE+K alteration of fgr groundmass. Dissem fgr LX  and fgr-mgr PY (~1%). CB crackle infill.
Fault zone. Brecciated. SE>CH>K>MT alteration. Transition zone between uphole mafic volcanic and downhole pale green foliated (sheared?) basalt. Consists of clasts of both.
Pale green SE>CH altered foliated amygdaloidal basalt. CBHM(ppl)HSPPYCP(trace) veining. Dissem fgr PX. Trace PY & CP <1%. Suspected Archean basalt. EOH.
green grey siltstone.

Pegmitite with thin intervals (xenoliths?) of metapelite. Coares grained with weak patchy sericite alteration. Pegmatite has altered garnets in it (dark spots).
High grade (metamorphic) garnet rich metapelite. Foliation is folded and undulating. Weak patchy chlorite-sericite alteration.
Pegmitite with thin intervals (xenoliths?) of metapelite. Coares grained with weak patchy sericite alteration. Pegmatite has altered garnets in it (dark spots).
